  "prompt": "What is an example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users?",
  "response": "One notable example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users is **Zoom**, the video conferencing tool. During the COVID-19 pandemic, Zoom capitalized on its integration capabilities with other platforms, particularly with educational and enterprise tools like Google Classroom and Microsoft Teams. \n\nBy allowing easy integration into these widely used platforms, Zoom was able to quickly onboard users from schools, businesses, and organizations that were already using those tools for communication and collaboration. This strategic positioning and integration boosted Zoom's user base significantly as the demand for virtual meetings skyrocketed during the pandemic. \n\nAnother example would be **Instagram**, which initially leveraged Facebook's platform for user authentication and social sharing. By allowing users to sign up using their Facebook accounts, Instagram was able to tap into Facebook's massive user base, facilitating rapid growth and adoption shortly after its launch. Later, Instagram's acquisition by Facebook in 2012 further solidified this growth strategy.",
